Class TwoSidedReserveFactor<T>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the factor's identity.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Factor<T>

    public class TwoSidedReserveFactor<T>
extends AbstractTwoSidedFactor<T>
    Max-sum "Two-sided reserve" factor. Given two sets of neighbors A = {a_1, ..., a_p} and B = {b_1, ..., b_q}, this factor tries to ensure that there are at least the same number of neighbors from the first set chosen than from the second one. That is, f(a_1, ..., a_p, b_1, ..., b_q) = 0 if (\sum_i a_i) (>=) (\sum_j b_j) or (-)\infty otherwise.
    Outgoing messages are computed in O(n log(n)) time. Where n is the number of elements in the biggest set. That is, n = max(p, q).
    Author:
    Toni Penya-Alba (tonipenya @ iiia.csic.es)
